{"article_id":"uVBj3dihSRnk36Ki","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Under deal","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"being negotiated ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"the debt ceiling would be increased until February 7 ,","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"sources say","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"Senate majority leader hopes","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"that Tuesday will be `` bright '' in Washington","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"A surge of optimism on Monday for a possible compromise","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"to end the partial government shutdown","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"and avoid a U.S. default as soon as this week got jolted by the sudden postponement of a White House meeting between President Barack Obama and congressional leaders .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"In a brief statement , the White House said","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"the meeting","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"announced earlier in the day","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"was put on hold","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"`` to allow leaders in the Senate time","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to continue making important progress '' toward a solution .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"It was unclear if the development signaled a problem","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"or was needed","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"to give more time for talks between Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid and his Republican counterpart , Mitch McConnell ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"to finish an agreement","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"that could win approval in the Senate and the House .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"Negotiations heated up","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"with the Democratic and Republican leaders signaling progress .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Both Reid and McConnell took to the Senate floor","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"to express optimism for a compromise on the twin priorities","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"that they expected to be reasonable and acceptable to both sides .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Reid 's tone remained positive","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"as night fell over the Capitol .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"`` We 've made tremendous progress , ''","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"that `` everyone just needs to be patient ''","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"and that `` perhaps tomorrow will be a bright day . ''","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"Key negotiators also maintained an upbeat posture","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"and financial markets ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"which Washington is watching very closely","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"considering their volatility over the political impasse ,","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"also ended the day higher","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"with Wall Street heartened by news of a possible deal , especially on the debt limit .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"At the same time , both sides noted","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"that nothing had been finalized","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"and the postponement of the meeting between congressional leaders and Obama and Vice President Joe Biden raised a new question mark in the process .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"Senate gets closer to a deal","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Senate gets closer to a deal","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"04:02 JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Will there be a deal ?","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"Will there be a deal ?","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"07:02 JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"Countdown to financial meltdown ?","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Countdown to financial meltdown ?","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"02:38 JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Sen. Ted Cruz takes on hecklers","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"Sen. Ted Cruz takes on hecklers","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"01:16","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"During a visit Monday to a local food pantry , Obama cited progress in the Senate negotiations","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"but also warned of what he called continued partisan brinkmanship by House Republicans","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"who `` continue to think","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"that somehow they can extract concessions","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"by keeping the government shut down","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"or by threatening default . ''","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"`` My hope is a spirit of cooperation will move us forward over the next few hours , ''","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"Obama said .","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"The failure of Congress","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"to authorize spending for the new fiscal year","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"triggered the shutdown on October 1 .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"Another deadline looms on Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"when the Treasury says","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"it will need Congress to raise the debt ceiling","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"so it can borrow more money","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"to pay all the government 's bills .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"During his visit to Martha 's Table in Washington , Obama said","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"the congressional leaders could `` solve this problem today . ''","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"He warned","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"that a default ,","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"in which the government would lack enough cash on hand","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"to pay down its debt obligations as well as other daily bills such as Social Security checks ,","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"`` could have a potentially devastating effect on our economy . ''","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"`` We 've already had a damaging effect on our economy","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"because of the shutdown , ''","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"he said .","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"`` That damage would be greatly magnified","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"if we do n't make sure","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"that government 's paying its bills ,","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"and that has to be decided this week . ''","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"The Treasury Department said","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"it will be unable to pay the government 's bills","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"unless the debt limit is increased by Thursday .","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"As reported by CNN 's Dana Bash and CNN Senior White House Correspondent Jim Acosta ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"the main sticking point involves how long an agreement would fund the government","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"to end the shutdown","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"and increase the debt limit .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"Democrats want the debt ceiling increase to extend as long as possible","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"to avoid similar showdowns in coming months .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"At the same time , they seek a temporary spending plan","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"to reopen the government","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"while formal budget negotiations work out a longer-term agreement","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"that can negate the impacts of the forced sequestration cuts .","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"Republicans , however , want a longer spending proposal","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"that would lock in the planned sequestration cuts in coming months , with a shorter debt ceiling extension","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"in order to negotiate further deficit-reduction measures .","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"Sen. Joe Manchin , D-West Virginia , and moderate GOP Sen. Susan Collins of Maine have spearheaded the bipartisan talks .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Separately , Republican Sen. Bob Corker of Tennessee also cited progress .","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"`` We 'll get this done .","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"We 're gon na get this done .","depth":15},{"id":113,"text":"I feel real confident , ''","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"Manchin said .","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"Manchin said","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"the goal was to get at least 65 Senate votes","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"-- which would mean 10 or more from Republicans --","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"to help Speaker John Boehner generate GOP backing in the House","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"despite certain opposition from the tea party conservative wing .","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"The two party leaders met twice in the morning and early afternoon ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"and they offered their optimistic assessments after their second face-to-face discussion .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"Boehner also dropped by McConnell 's office","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"to get an update on the talks ,","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"his aide confirmed .","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"Democratic sources told Bash and CNN 's Deirdre Walsh","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"that the proposal under consideration by Reid and McConnell would fund the government through January 15 ,","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"allowing it to reopen for at least three months or so .","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"At the same time , negotiations on a budget for the full fiscal year would have a deadline of some time in December ,","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"the sources said .","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"Meanwhile , the debt ceiling would be increased through February 7","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"to put off the threat of default for almost four months ,","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"according to sources in both parties .","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"The budget negotiations were expected to address deficit reduction measures","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"and therefore could impact when the debt limit would need to be increased again .","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"In addition , provisions","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"involving Obama 's signature health care reforms","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"could be included ,","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"such as strengthening verification measures for people","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"seeking federal subsidies","depth":17},{"id":140,"text":"to help them purchase health insurance","depth":17},{"id":141,"text":"required by the 2010 Affordable Care Act ,","depth":16},{"id":142,"text":"the sources said .","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"Another possible change to the health care reforms would delay a fee on employers , unions and other plan sponsors","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"that raise money","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"to compensate insurance companies","depth":15},{"id":146,"text":"for taking on high-risk customers in the early years of Obamacare .","depth":15},{"id":147,"text":"CNN political analyst John Avlon said Monday","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"that Democrats wanted to press what they perceive as an advantage over Republicans on how the public is perceiving the latest round of Washington budget and deficit brinkmanship .","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"`` What 's behind it ( are ) poll numbers","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"that saw Republicans getting their butt kicked","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"because of this whole gamesmanship , ''","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"Avlon said .","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"Mindful that the Thursday debt deadline is days away ,","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"House Republican leaders are considering all their options","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"even as Republican and Democratic Senate leaders try to craft a deal on the debt ceiling ,","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"said a GOP leadership aide ,","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"speaking on the condition of anonymity .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":315,"left":0,"right":314